CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a programming language used to style HTML elements. It controls the appearance of web pages, including fonts, colors, layouts, and more. CSS separates the content (HTML) from the presentation (CSS), making websites easier to maintain and update.

Role in Web Development:

Presentation: CSS defines how HTML elements are displayed on the screen.
Structure: It helps create visually appealing and organized web pages.
Maintainability: Separating content from presentation improves code readability and manageability.
Responsiveness: CSS can be used to create responsive designs that adapt to different screen sizes.
