CSS
/* styles.css */

body {
    background-color: lightblue;
    color: white;
    font-size: 20px;
}
Use code with caution.

Explanation of CSS Code:

body: Selects the entire body of the HTML document.
background-color: lightblue;: Sets the background color of the body to light blue.
color: white;: Sets the text color of the body to white.
font-size: 20px;: Sets the font size of the body text to 20 pixels.
Effect on HTML Elements:

The background of the entire page will be light blue.
All text within the body will be white.
The font size of all text within the body will be 20 pixels.
Additional Notes:

You can create more specific styles by targeting individual elements or classes using CSS selectors.
CSS properties can be combined to achieve various effects.
CSS can be used to create complex layouts and animations.
